## Implementation Guide

### Data Sources

#### Maintenance Record Detail
- **API Endpoint**: `GET /api/fleet/maintenance-records/{id}/`
- **Fields Used**:
  - `id` - Record ID/number
  - `vehicle` - Vehicle the maintenance is for
  - `maintenance_type` - Type of maintenance service
  - `status` - Current status of the maintenance
  - `scheduled_date` - When the maintenance is scheduled
  - `description` - Maintenance description
  - `priority` - Priority level
  - `estimated_duration_hours` - Expected duration
  - `work_order_number` - Reference number
  - `location` - Service location
  - `technician` - Assigned technician
  - `cost` - Total cost

#### Vehicle Information
- **API Endpoint**: Same record endpoint or `GET /api/fleet/vehicles/{id}/`
- **Fields Used**: Vehicle details via relation from maintenance record

#### KPI Cards
- **Fields Used**:
  - `priority` - Priority level (High/Medium/Low)
  - `estimated_duration_hours` - Expected duration
  - `cost` - Total cost
  - `technician` - Assigned technician

#### Maintenance History
- **API Endpoint**: `GET /api/fleet/maintenance-records/history/?vehicle={vehicle_id}&start={start_date}&end={end_date}`
- **Documentation Reference**: History endpoint mentioned in API actions section
- **Purpose**: Shows previous maintenance for this vehicle

#### Work Order
- **API Endpoint**: `GET /api/fleet/maintenance-records/{id}/work_order_pdf/`
- **Documentation Reference**: Work order HTML endpoint mentioned in API actions section
- **Purpose**: Provides access to work order document

### Action Buttons
All buttons match actions documented in the maintenance.md file:

- **Edit**:
  - **API**: `PUT/PATCH /api/fleet/maintenance-records/{id}/`
  - **Documentation Reference**: Update endpoint in base endpoints section

- **Complete**:
  - **API**: `POST /api/fleet/maintenance-records/{id}/complete/`
  - **Request Body (Optional)**: `{ "cost": <decimal> }`
  - **Documentation Reference**: Complete action in actions section

- **Reschedule**:
  - **API**: `POST /api/fleet/maintenance-records/{id}/schedule/`
  - **Request Body**: `{ "scheduled_date": "YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SSZ" }`
  - **Documentation Reference**: Schedule/Reschedule action in actions section

- **Cancel**:
  - **API**: `POST /api/fleet/maintenance-records/{id}/cancel/`
  - **Documentation Reference**: Cancel action in actions section

- **Delete**:
  - **API**: `DELETE /api/fleet/maintenance-records/{id}/`
  - **Documentation Reference**: Delete endpoint in base endpoints section

### API Alignment
All endpoints and fields used in this design match the documentation in maintenance.md:
- `GET /api/fleet/maintenance-records/{id}/` - Get record details
- `PUT/PATCH /api/fleet/maintenance-records/{id}/` - Update record
- `DELETE /api/fleet/maintenance-records/{id}/` - Delete record
- `POST /api/fleet/maintenance-records/{id}/complete/` - Complete record
- `POST /api/fleet/maintenance-records/{id}/schedule/` - Reschedule record
- `POST /api/fleet/maintenance-records/{id}/cancel/` - Cancel record
- `GET /api/fleet/maintenance-records/{id}/work_order_pdf/` - Get work order
- `GET /api/fleet/maintenance-records/history/` - Get maintenance history
